column4: <content>Ad[ Addendum] Murder of Innocents. Christina of Sweden: 1656 May Antwerp. Only listed cases with works to be sent to Rome. She kept mostly Italian pictures, portraits among them: Morus by Holbein, but not smaller Flemish XVI paintings as can be seen from her Italian catalogue of Rome probably c. 1689 (Granberg Appendix III) [= Olof Granberg, Catalogue raisonné de tableaux anciens inconnus jusqu'ici dans les collections privées de la Suède : I : contenant 500 tableaux, prinicpalement des écoles hollandaise et flamande du XVIIe siècle, Stockholm: Samson & Wallin, 1886]</content>
